{"word":"ἐκπέμπω","slug":"ἐκπέμπω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐκπέμπω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ψω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b>of persons, <i>to send out</i> or <i>forth from</i> a place, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to bring out by calling, call</i> or <i>fetch out</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to go forth, depart</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>to send forth, dispatch</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><i>to send away, cast out</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <i>to divorce</i> a wife, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>:—so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of things, <i>to send out, send abroad</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to send forth, give out</i>, <el>σέλας</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}